oblade","quantity":3,"equipped":false},{"id":"eq-z-8","name":"Robot Dog Corpse?","quantity":1,"equipped":false},{"id":"eq-z-9","name":"Mars","quantity":2,"equipped":false},{"id":"eq-z-10","name":"Perk","quantity":1,"equipped":false},{"id":"eq-z-11","name":"Nanodoc","quantity":6,"equipped":false},{"id":"eq-z-12","name":"Spike Strip","quantity":1,"equipped":false},{"id":"eq-z-13","name":"Sticky Grenade","quantity":0,"equipped":false},{"id":"eq-z-14","name":"Rope","quantity":1,"equipped":false},{"id":"eq-z-15","name":"Lock Picks","quantity":1,"equipped":false},{"id":"eq-z-16","name":"Grappling Hooks","quantity":2,"equipped":false},{"id":"eq-z-17","name":"Bug Detector","quantity":1,"equipped":false},{"id":"eq-z-18","name":"Hypospray (For Nanodoc)","quantity":1,"equipped":false},{"id":"eq-z-19","name":"Frictionless Spray","quantity":1,"equipped":false},{"id":"eq-z-20","name":"Thing I Want -> Something That Gives Me Hard-Knuckle","quantity":1,"equipped":false},{"id":"eq-z-21","name":"Overclock Hex","quantity":3,"equipped":false},{"id":"eq-z-22","name":"Rishad's Personal Journal","quantity":1,"equipped":false},{"id":"eq-z-23","name":"Encrypted Hard Drive From Rishad's Room","quantity":1,"equipped":false},{"id":"eq-z-24","name":"Poker Chip With Ai Fragment","quantity":1,"equipped":false},{"id":"eq-z-25","name":"Lil Birdie Herringbone - A Croc's Best Friend","quantity":1,"equipped":false},{"id":"eq-z-26","name":"Brass Knuckles","quantity":1,"equipped":true}]	{"satoshi":34055}	[{"id":"zarge-feat-1","name":"CALL IT - Brutal Focus","source":"Hardcase","description":"Uses Bonus Action for the Turn — DC10 Concentration"},{"id":"zarge-feat-2","name":"Pugilist","source":"Hardcase","description":"Uses My Bonus Action"},{"id":"zarge-feat-3","name":"Bonus Action - Brutal Focus","source":"Hardcase","description":"As a bonus action at the start of your turn you can re-designate or maintain your Brutal Focus target (a creature within 18 metres that you can see), sustaining the concentration without spending your full action. You must still make a DC 10 Concentration saving throw if you take damage while Brutal Focus is active."},{"id":"zarge-feat-4","name":"Unarmored Defense","source":"Hardcase","description":"While you are not wearing any armour, your Armour Class equals 10 + your Dexterity modifier + your Constitution modifier."},{"id":"zarge-feat-5","name":"Second Wind","source":"Hardcase","description":"On your turn you can use a bonus action to regain hit points equal to 1d10 + your Hardcase level. Once you use this feature you must finish a short or long rest before you can use it again. You gain 2 uses per rest at 10th level and 3 uses per rest at 15th level."},{"id":"zarge-feat-6","name":"Striker","source":"Fighting Style","description":"Your unarmed strikes count as finesse weapons, deal 1d4 bludgeoning damage (plus Strength or Dexterity modifier), and are treated as light weapons. Once per turn when you hit with an unarmed strike you may attempt to Shove or Grapple the target as a bonus action."},{"id":"zarge-feat-7","name":"Takedown","source":"MMA","description":"Expert wrestling technique: on a successful Grapple check you may immediately knock the target prone. The prone target must spend all of its movement on its next turn to stand, or remain prone."},{"id":"zarge-feat-8","name":"Trip (With Tail)","source":"MMA","description":"Using your powerful tail you sweep an opponent's legs as a bonus action after hitting with a melee attack. Make a Strength (Athletics) check contested by the target's Strength (Athletics) or Dexterity (Acrobatics). On a success the target is knocked prone."},{"id":"zarge-feat-9","name":"Wrist Strike","source":"MMA","description":"A precision strike targeting the weapon hand. Spend 1 superiority die (1d6): add the die to the attack's damage, and the target must succeed on a DC 13 Strength saving throw or drop one held item of your choice."},{"id":"zarge-feat-10","name":"Maneuvering Attack","source":"MMA","description":"Spend 1 superiority die (1d6): add the die to the attack's damage, then choose one friendly creature that can see or hear you. That creature can use its reaction to move up to half its speed without provoking opportunity attacks."},{"id":"zarge-feat-11","name":"Vitruvian Sprint Boost","source":"MMA","description":"Your Vitruvian synthetic leg muscles can burst into explosive speed. As a bonus action you double your movement speed until the end of your turn and may move through enemy-occupied spaces without provoking opportunity attacks. Once per short rest."},{"id":"zarge-feat-12","name":"Acute Senses","source":"Leviathan Race","description":"+3 to Perception rolls"},{"id":"zarge-feat-13","name":"Carnivore","source":"Leviathan Race","description":"You are unable to digest plant-based sugars and must subsist on a purely meat diet. You cannot benefit from rations or food that is not primarily meat-based."},{"id":"zarge-feat-14","name":"Menacing Maw","source":"Leviathan Race","description":"You can make Strength (Intimidation) checks instead of Charisma (Intimidation) checks against targets within 6 metres, with advantage if grappling them. You can also bite grappled targets: an armour-piercing simple melee attack that deals 2d6 piercing + STR modifier (2d8 at level 6, 2d10 at level 11, 2d12 at level 17)."},{"id":"zarge-feat-15","name":"Reptile Brain","source":"Leviathan Race","description":"Mind hackers have a hard time cracking in. You gain advantage on saving throws against any mind hacks."}]	[]	[]	[]	0	16	2026-03-16 06:17:16.491068	2026-03-16 06:17:16.491068	The Reverent	0	4	{"acuteOlfaction":false,"darkvision":true,"macrovision":false,"microvision":false,"penetration":false,"spectrum":false}	\N	2026-03-16 06:17:16.49	/objects/uploads/0dd9c7b2-416e-4d34-8433-14be97d9167c
