st you, roll a d20 and use that as their roll instead. Statistically Improbable: once per session, when you fail any roll, you can automatically make it a success. Uncanny Survival: once per session, when a roll that targets you succeeds, you can automatically make it fail."},{"id":"feat-2","name":"Underworld Etiquette","source":"Outlaw","description":"You have been steeped in the customs, codes, and unwritten rules that govern criminal organisations — loyalty oaths, tribute expectations, territory respect, and the art of the introduction. You gain proficiency in Underworld Etiquette checks, allowing you to navigate criminal hierarchies smoothly, avoid deadly insults, and recognise when you are (or are not) welcome."},{"id":"feat-3","name":"Shady Contact +1","source":"Crook+Outlaw","description":"Through the combined influence of your Crook class and Outlaw background, you have cultivated an additional contact deep in the criminal underworld. This contact can provide shelter, fence stolen goods, trade sensitive information, and arrange access to restricted or illegal equipment. Work with your GM to define who they are and what organisation they represent."},{"id":"feat-4","name":"Cunning Action","source":"Crook","description":"You can use a bonus action to take the Dash, Disengage, or Hide action."},{"id":"feat-5","name":"Sneak Attack","source":"Crook","description":"Once per turn you can deal extra damage to one creature you hit with a finesse or ranged weapon if you have advantage on the attack roll. The extra damage is 1d6, and increases as you gain Crook levels: 2d6 at 3rd, 3d6 at 5th, 4d6 at 7th, 5d6 at 9th, 6d6 at 11th, 7d6 at 13th, 8d6 at 15th, 9d6 at 17th, 10d6 at 19th. You don't need advantage if another enemy of the target is within 1.5 metres of it."},{"id":"feat-6","name":"Assassinate","source":"Hitman","description":"During your first turn of combat you have advantage on attack rolls against any creature that has not yet taken a turn. Any hit you score against a surprised creature is automatically a critical hit."},{"id":"feat-7","name":"Prey Dossier","source":"Hitman","description":"You can spend 1 hour gathering intel (in person or through information networks) to compile a dossier on a single target. Once complete, you have advantage on all Intelligence and Wisdom checks related to that target and always know their general location as long as you have access to any data network. You may only maintain one active dossier at a time."}]	[]	[]	[]	0	18	2026-03-16 03:56:09.063344	2026-03-16 06:57:16.478	The Reverent	633	-2	{"spectrum": true, "darkvision": false, "macrovision": false, "microvision": false, "penetration": false, "acuteOlfaction": false}	\N	\N	\N
